edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.utils

Class UMLModelUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.utils.UMLModelUtils
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DSEMLUtils

    public class UMLModelUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    Collection of functions to ease querying and computing sets of elements from a UML model (e.g., retrieval of all constraints that are owned and inherited).
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Sebastian

      • collectConstraints

        public static java.util.ArrayList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Constraint> collectConstraints(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Activity workingPrinciple)
        Returns the constraints associated with a particular activity / working principle.

        This will return all constraints associated with a working principle at any level of inheritance.

        Parameters:
        workingPrinciple - The working principle to collect constraints from.
        Returns:
        A set of inherited and owned constraints of an activity.

      • findClassifierByQualifiedName

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Classifier findClassifierByQualifiedName(java.lang.String qualifiedName,
                                                            org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Namespace startingPoint)
        Performs a depth first search to try and find a classifier with the given qualified name.

        This function is similar to findElementByQualifiedName(String, Namespace) but specifically searches for an instance of a UML classifier rather than an element.

        Parameters:
        qualifiedName - The qualified name of the element.
        startingPoint - The starting point from which to start the search on.
        Returns:
        The classifier if found, null otherwise.

      • getStringValue

        public static java.lang.String getStringValue(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.ValueSpecification vs)
        Attempts to find a string representation of a value specification.

        This function is currently aware of LiteralString, LiteralInteger, LiteralReal, LiteralBoolean and OpaqueExpression. For any other type it will return the empty string.

        Parameters:
        vs - The value specification.
        Returns:
        A string representation of the value specification or the empty string.

      • getProperty

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property getProperty(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element parent,
                                        java.lang.String propertyName)
        Extracts a property of a classifier.

        This routine goes through the set of owned properties and returns the one with the specified name. If the property was not found in the set of owned properties, the search is repeated by going through the set of inherited properties as well.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - Name of the property.
        Returns:
        The UML Property object if found, null otherwise.

      • getParameter

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Parameter getParameter(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Activity parent,
                                          java.lang.String parameterName)
        Extracts a parameter from an activity.

        Note that this function will also search through the inherited members. This is not compliant with the UML spec, but is useful at least within our context.

        Parameters:
        parent - The parent activity.
        parameterName - The name of the parameter.
        Returns:
        The parameter object or null if not found.
